Your best bet is to read thru all the threads here on this message board about items to buy.  I know I have replied to numerous postings on this subject.  But since you need help and I'm pretty bored, I'll give some advice.  First and foremost, buy any item with high wisdom stats.  Druids are wisdom based toons and need the wisdom.  I recommend starting low end and eventually work your way up to better items later.  At level 19, you're not really in a position to really make any money, and won't be able too until the late 40's, when you'll be able to start farming items like Griffon and Anaconda meat and Plant Shoots in Jaggedpine.

You can still shop the Bazaar and find decent items for sale at decent prices up there if you have the plat and the patients to look for it. There's so much out there for a Druid to wear and use, it's unbelieveable.

Best of luck.

